Task Description:

Deploy a simple web application using AWS code commit, code build and deploy & access via browser and automate via codepipeline.
-------------------------------------------
CodeCommit – Store your app code.
CodeBuild – Build your application (optional if no build needed).
CodeDeploy – Deploy to EC2 or ECS.
CodePipeline – Automate the flow: commit → build → deploy
---------------------------------------------
Steps:

1. Create n EC2 instance  and under advanced details add the commands to install httpd and codedeployagent 
Name - task-instance

2. Create IAM Role with AmazonEC2forAWSCodeDeploy and attach it to task-instance
Role Name - Task-instance-Role 

3. 


